text=!!Honorary Lifetime Membership Committee%0a%0a# %25outline%25 Purpose%0a##The Honorary Lifetime Membership Committee is created each term to fulfill the following duties:%0a### to solicit nominations for persons to receive an Honorary Lifetime Membership;%0a### to investigate all nominees; and%0a### to recommend to Council, those whom they see deserving of an Honorary Lifetime membership.%0a%0a# Membership%0a##The Committee will consist of the following:%0a### the Director of Internal Affairs, as chair; and%0a### 1 to 3 Council appointees.%0a## If one of the members of the Committee is to be considered for an Honorary Lifetime Membership, then he shall resign his membership and will be replaced by an individual appointed by Council.%0a%0a# Procedures%0a## The Honorary Lifetime Membership Committee shall be formed within the first six weeks of the term. The Committee shall meet at least once after the close of nominations, further meetings being at the discretion of the Committee. All meetings of the Committee are to be closed and confidential.%0a## At the beginning of each term (and possibly at following meetings), an announcement will be made regarding nominations of candidates for this award.%0a## There shall be a period of no fewer than two weeks during which nominations can be received. This period shall not extend past the tenth week of classes. There shall be a notice of nominations posted in the Society office at that time. Nominations should include a description of the candidate's contributions.%0a## If, at the first meeting after the close of nominations, the Committee feels that one or more deserving persons have been overlooked in that a nomination was not received for said persons, the Committee will:%0a### obtain a description of said person’s contributions; and%0a### consider said persons as nominees in company with the gathered nominations.%0a## The Committee will then:%0a### thoroughly investigate all candidates, including discussions with faculty, administration, students (where applicable) and the other stream's Council (note: this does not imply the other stream must confirm the Committee's recommendations); and%0a### submit a report with recommendations of the recipient(s) to Council by the last meeting of the term for individual confirmation, including a list of names and descriptions of the candidates' involvement.%0a## Nominations of individuals not recommended by the committee for the award shall be maintained in confidence.%0a%0a# Criteria for Nominees%0a## The Nominee must:%0a### be graduating or have otherwise completed their studies; and%0a### have contributed significantly for most terms spent on campus, including not only contributions to math activities but also to other activities which have enhanced student life.%0a%0aNote: The Honorary Lifetime Membership Award is meant as a prestigious and distinctive award. In order to maintain the significance of this award the Committee should exercise conservatism in recommending nominees to Council, but should not hesitate to do so where the nominee is deserving of the award.
